        "Golden cadence of poesy.",
        "If in any composition much attention was paid to the flow of the rhythm, it was said (at least in the 14th and 15th centuries) to be cadence.",
        "These parting numbers, cadenced by my grief."
    ],
    "etymology": "[OE. cadence, cadens, LL. cadentia a falling, fr. L. cadere to fall; cf. F. cadence, It. cadenza. See Chance.]"
